    • Constructor Detail

      • IndirectTarget

        public IndirectTarget(MethodSubSignature targetMethod,
                      int argIndex)
        Creates a new direct method invocation. The signature of this indirect target references a method that was called earlier, and which received the object on which the callback is invoked. This constructor assumes that the earlier method has created an object which is passed the current method as an argument.
        Parameters:
        targetMethod - The method with which the original callback was registered
        argIndex - The index of the argument that holds the object that holds the callback or next step of the indirect invocation

      • IndirectTarget

        public IndirectTarget(VirtualEdgesSummaries.InstanceinvokeSource source)
        Creates a new indirect target as an indirection from a method that was previously considered a source
        Parameters:
        source - The source from which to create the indirect target
